Kwaito king Arthur Mafokate has been slapped with a combined R3.7-million lawsuit by his ex-girlfriend and singer Cici. The singer, real name Busisiwe Thwala, filed an application at the South Gauteng High Court in Joburg on Wednesday, claiming an amount of R2.5-million in damages for injuries she sustained following an incident during which Mafokate allegedly dragged her with his car. TO READ MORE OF THIS AND OTHER STORIES GRAB A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE.